President Obama has nominated Scott M. Matheson, Jr. to the United States Court of Appeals for the Tenth Circuit. Matheson is currently a professor at the S.J. Quinney College of Law at the University of Utah and has a strong background in both academia and law. He has served as Dean of the Law School and also taught at Harvard University's Kennedy School of Government. Matheson has previously held public service positions, including United States Attorney for the District of Utah and chair of the Utah Mine Safety Commission. He is a sixth-generation Utahn and holds degrees from Stanford University, Oxford University (as a Rhodes Scholar), and Yale Law School.